        <odd id="ref2">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>This collection is cross-listed with the 
                <extref ns2:actuate="onLoad" ns2:show="new" ns2:href="http://www.amphilsoc.org/mole/view?docId=ead/Mss.973.2.M31-ead.xml">Pennsylvania Non-Importation Collection (Mss.973.2.M31)</extref>. The finding aid for that collection contains additional details on this collection. In summary, part of the collection contains a series of letters that John Hughes, the appointed collector of the stamp tax in 1765, wrote detailing his experience.The letters provide an account of Philadelphia's reaction to the Stamp Act from the persepctive of Hughes.</p>
